Information Gathering and Enumeration Lab

Objective
To perform reconnaissance, service enumeration, information gathering, and vulnerability assessment on a target system in a controlled laboratory environment using industry-standard cybersecurity tools.

Tools Used

* Kali Linux
* Nmap
* SMBClient
* Enum4linux
* theHarvester
* Nessus Essentials

Activities Performed
1. Host Discovery
Performed host discovery using Nmap to determine whether the target system was active and reachable

Command Used
nmap -sn testphp.vulnweb.com


Result
The target host responded successfully, confirming that it was online and available for further assessment.

2. Service Detection
Conducted service and version detection to identify open ports and running services on the target system.

Command Used
nmap -sV testphp.vulnweb.com

Result
The target was reachable; however, all scanned ports were filtered, indicating the possible presence of firewall or security filtering mechanisms.

3. SMB Enumeration
Attempted to enumerate SMB services, shares, users, and system information.

Commands Used
smbclient -L //testphp.vulnweb.com -N

enum4linux -a testphp.vulnweb.com


Result
SMB enumeration was unsuccessful because the target did not respond to SMB requests, indicating restricted or unavailable SMB services.

 4. Open Source Intelligence (OSINT)
Gathered publicly available information about the target domain using theHarvester.

Command Used
theHarvester -d testphp.vulnweb.com -b all

Result
No email addresses were discovered. However, useful URLs related to the target were identified.

Discovered Resources

* http://testphp.vulnweb.com/
* http://testphp.vulnweb.com/login.php
* https://testphp.vulnweb.com/

5. Vulnerability Assessment
Installed and configured Nessus Essentials to perform vulnerability scanning.

Activities

* Installed Nessus
* Started Nessus service
* Verified Nessus status
* Performed a vulnerability assessment scan

Result
The scan completed successfully and reported no vulnerabilities on the selected target.

Skills Demonstrated

* Network Reconnaissance
* Host Discovery
* Service Detection
* Service Enumeration
* SMB Enumeration
* OSINT (Open Source Intelligence)
* Vulnerability Assessment
* Security Analysis
* Nessus Administration

